info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 09 at 2:11PM MST until December 10 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 PM MST SUNDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph possible. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, North Snowy Range Foothills, and South Laramie Range. This includes Bordeaux along Interstate 25 and Arlington along Interstate 80. * WHEN...From Saturday evening through Sunday evening. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
